  {\text{I    }}S(i) = {\text{F, I, L, M, V,}} \hfill \\
  {\text{E   }}S(i) = {\text{D, E, H, K, N, Q, R,}} \hfill \\
  {\text{A   }}S(i) = {\text{S, T, Y, C, W, G, P, A}}, \hfill \\ 
\end{gathered}  \right.
\]
\end{document}  where S(i) is the letter in the ith position in the protein primary sequence, and F(S(i)) is the substitution for S(i). Since the hydropathy profile can detect more evolutionary relationships, in the next section, we analyzed the new protein sequence containing three letters through different mathematical methods.

